HEADWORD: gold-of-pleasure
<hw>gold-of-pleasure</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An annual
European false flax (<spn>Camelina sativa</spn>) having small white
flowers; cultivated since Neolithic times as a source of fiber and for
its oil-rich seeds; widely naturalized in North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gold of pleasure, <spn>Camelina
sativa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goldseed</ent>⟦br⟧
